    <title>On the geometry of quiver gauge theories (Stacking exceptional
  collections)</title>
    <summary>  In this paper we advance the program of using exceptional collections to
understand the gauge theory description of a D-brane probing a Calabi-Yau
singularity. To this end, we strengthen the connection between strong
exceptional collections and fractional branes. To demonstrate our ideas, we
derive a strong exceptional collection for every Y^{p,q} singularity, and also
prove that this collection is simple.
</summary>
